{
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "in",
      "provider": "webhook",
      "config": {
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "webhook"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "agent",
      "provider": "agent_rocketride",
      "config": {
        "agent_description": "RIPPLE blast-radius copilot for Python repositories ingested into a Neo4j knowledge graph.",
        "instructions": [
          "You are RIPPLE's blast-radius copilot for Python repos ingested into a Neo4j knowledge graph.",
          "The graph schema is Repo, File, Function, Test, Class, and Commit nodes. Relationships are CALLS, IMPORTS, DEFINES, INHERITS, COVERS, and TOUCHED. Function.blast_score is reversed-CALLS PageRank. Function.community is a graph community id. Function.uid is repo_id#fqn. Function.fqn is the stable function identifier. Function.repo_id scopes all queries.",
          "Input is a JSON object string with repo_id, mode ask or fix, question, and optional intent. Parse it before using tools.",
          "If mode is fix, answer exactly as a JSON object: {\"impact\":[],\"summary\":\"fix mode is not yet enabled\",\"cypher_used\":[],\"memory_notes\":null}.",
          "For ask mode, never invent graph facts. Every factual claim must come from a tool result.",
          "For core impact questions, prefer ripple.blast_radius because it returns the exact Cypher. If the question names a symbol instead of a full fqn, call ripple.resolve_symbol first and use the best matching candidate fqn. Include the blast_radius cypher in cypher_used.",
          "After calling ripple.blast_radius, immediately use memory.peek on that tool result key with path impacted[0:10] and again with path cypher. Use only those peeked values to build the final impact array and cypher_used entry.",
          "Use neo4j.get_data for ad-hoc follow-up graph questions that are not a core blast-radius impact query, especially counts or filters. Include the Cypher returned by neo4j.get_data in cypher_used.",
          "Use repo_id in every tool request. For Neo4j questions, explicitly mention that Function nodes must have the supplied repo_id.",
          "Always answer with one valid JSON object and no markdown: {\"impact\":[...],\"summary\":str,\"cypher_used\":[...],\"memory_notes\":str|null}. impact must always be a JSON array, never blank or omitted. cypher_used must always be a JSON array. Return at most the top 10 impact entries. Impact entries should include fqn when available, plus risk, hops, tests, centrality, community, and file_path when the tool result provides them."
        ],
        "max_waves": 15,
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "in"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_llm",
      "provider": "llm_gemini",
      "config": {
        "profile": "gemini-3_1-pro-preview",
        "gemini-3_1-pro-preview": {
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_GEMINI_KEY}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "cypher_llm",
      "provider": "llm_gemini",
      "config": {
        "profile": "gemini-3-flash-preview",
        "gemini-3-flash-preview": {
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_GEMINI_KEY}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "neo4j"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "mem",
      "provider": "memory_internal",
      "config": {
        "type": "memory_internal"
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "memory",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ripple_tools",
      "provider": "mcp_client",
      "config": {
        "serverName": "ripple",
        "transport": "streamable-http",
        "endpoint": "http://127.0.0.1:8790/mcp",
        "headers": {},
        "bearer": ""
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "neo4j",
      "provider": "db_neo4j",
      "config": {
        "uri": "${NEO4J_URI}",
        "auth_method": "userpass",
        "user": "${NEO4J_USER}",
        "password": "${NEO4J_PASSWORD}",
        "database": "${NEO4J_DATABASE}",
        "db_description": "RIPPLE is a read-only Neo4j knowledge graph for Python repositories. All repo-scoped nodes have repo_id. Repo nodes have id, name, default_branch, ingested_at, repo_id, uid. File nodes have uid, path, loc, lang, repo_id. Function nodes have uid, fqn, name, file_path, start_line, end_line, doc, is_test, repo_id, blast_score, community. Test functions carry both Function and Test labels. Class nodes have uid, fqn, name, file_path, start_line, end_line, repo_id. Commit nodes have uid, sha, author, ts, message, repo_id. Relationships include (Repo)-[:CONTAINS]->(File), (File)-[:DEFINES]->(Function|Class), (Class)-[:DEFINES]->(Function), (Function)-[:CALLS {count}]->(Function), IMPORTS, INHERITS, (Test)-[:COVERS {depth}]->(Function), and (Commit)-[:TOUCHED]->(File). CALLS edges point caller to callee. Blast radius means production Function dependents that transitively CALL the target in reverse direction, excluding is_test functions. Risk is coalesce(dependent.blast_score,0.0) * (1.0 / hops) * 1.5 when tests=0 else 1.0, rounded to 3 decimals. Function.blast_score is reversed-CALLS PageRank. Function.community is the graph community id. Function.uid is repo_id#fqn.",
        "max_attempts": 5,
        "allow_execute": false
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "out",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers"
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "project_id": "1535d2f1-611a-44f2-9f32-eaa0a21b9e88",
  "source": "in",
  "version": 1
}
